‘Parry, in his Introduction to Terence, p. nvn sets down three rules which would serve to explain the admissibility of hiatus, vin: hiatus,- he says, is justified,

Setting aeide the third rule, which has indeed a general value for all Latin poets, we confine ourselves to a more detailed discussion of

Hiatus is justified: (a) where the line is divided among two or more speakers, (b) by caesura.
